          "date": "2017-07-27 02:59:51.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-07-27 03:01:59.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-9410 ldiskfs: read bitmap with lock",
        "message": "LU-9410 ldiskfs: read bitmap with lock\n\nThe old logic will set the bitmap buffer head as 'bitmap_uptodate'\nbefore the buffer head is read from disk. If others also want to\nread such bitmap during such interval by race, then the latter\nmay get uninitialized bitmap, as to some fake data corruption.\n\nThis patch makes the bitmap reader to take lock on the bitmap buffer\nhead before checking whether it is up-to-date or not. Because the\nfirstly bitmap reader will hold such lock when loading the bitmap\nfrom disk, then it will prevent the others accessing uninitialized\nbitmap. It may be not the perfect solution, but we can use it to\nresolve our current trouble.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I3485684aa100a7cf67d71f2ac9b9a00484983f36\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
